The intitial brain state. Subject factors and their corresponding brain states may heavily influence or even completely flip (polarity-opposing) tDCS effects. For example, fatigue/attention{\~{}}ongoing alpa activity, habituation{\~{}}neural adaptation, task processing vs. resting state, etc.















